==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unworship
<hw>Un*wor"ship</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>worship</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deprive of worship
or due honor; to dishonor.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Wyclif.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unworship</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unworship
<hw>Un*wor"ship</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>un-</ets> not +
<ets>worship</ets>.]</ety> <def>Lack of worship or respect;
dishonor.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Gower.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unworth</ent>⟦br⟧
